{
  "stem": "12337.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had on a huge coat with pockets, and he would put the food in his pocket.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he couldn't give us much because he was very poor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A piece of bread. maybe a little bit of soup, a bottle of water.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he would try once a day or maybe every other day-- come into the barn like he would be getting hay out for the horses, you know?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had always-- not just to come in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He always came out doing something that it wouldn't be suspicious for anybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he would give us that stuff.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And once a night he gave us a pot for elimination and that was the most-- that was the most dangerous part of the whole 18 months of hiding because once a night the same thing.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He would call the dog, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Briskov ?], and the dog would be running around all over, making sure there was no one around and-- and he would go from the outside of the barn, Pavlo, and take out a piece of the sled.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father would crawl out with the pot and not-- not far from there there was a little river, and he would throw it into the river.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but it was a very dangerous thing to do because you never knew if anybody-- even though the dog-- you know, it's still a dog.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so when he could-- of course, when he couldn't it would go on for more than a day-- or, at night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was usually at that that would happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The piece of bread that we had, we had to share with mice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The mice were always around.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were our best buddies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They wanted the bread.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
